Interference in a thin film with air on both sides (nair≈1) and film‐index n=1.36, thickness t=380 nm, gives for the reflected beam a π‐phase flip on the front‐surface reflection only.  Hence the condition for constructive reflection is

    2 n t = (m+½) λ,    m=0,1,2,…

so

    λm = 2 n t / (m+½).

Numerically 2 n t = 2·1.36·380 nm ≃1 033.6 nm, so

  for m=0: λ0 =1 033.6 nm/0.5 ≃2 067 nm (IR, not visible)  
  for m=1: λ1 =1 033.6 nm/1.5 ≃689 nm (red)  
  for m=2: λ2 =1 033.6 nm/2.5 ≃413 nm (violet–blue)  
  for m≥3: λm<300 nm (UV)  

Thus the two visible reflected maxima occur at about 690 nm (deep red) and 413 nm (violet–blue).
